%S A397472 1,16,496,19456,860656,40950016,2046002176,105871998976,5624778793456,
%T A397472 305037572805376,16817115765450496,939739255564926976,
%U A397472 53106743097015632896,3029913225835118903296,174285123777246371086336,10096449196416958339219456
%N A397472 a(n) = 64^n * [z^n] 2F1(1/4, 1/4; 1; z)^4.
%C A397472 Lemniscatic fourth-power endpoint at the CM point j = 1728. This is the self-convolution of b(n) = binomial(2*n,n)^3 (A002897), i.e. the endpoint d = 4 of the lemniscatic symmetric-power ladder.
%C A397472 In Shvets' modular-form interpretation, the multiplier is trivial and the relevant Hecke operator is the classical U_p + p^5*V_p. Consequently, for every odd prime p and all m, r >= 1, the paper (see Links) proves a(m*p^r) == a(m*p^(r-1)) (mod p^(5*r)).
%C A397472 The exponent 5*r is best possible: already a(3) - a(1) = 19440 = 3^5 * 80, with 3 not dividing 80, so the congruence cannot be uniformly strengthened to modulus p^(5*r+1).
%H A397472 Alex Shvets, <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.20940394">A Sharp Fifth-Power Supercongruence Tower for a Lemniscatic Convolution Sequence</a>, Zenodo, 2026.
%F A397472 a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} binomial(2*k,k)^3 * binomial(2*(n-k),n-k)^3.
%F A397472 G.f.: Sum_{n>=0} a(n)*x^n = hypergeom([1/4,1/4],[1],64*x)^4.
%F A397472 Equivalently, Sum_{n>=0} a(n)*x^n = ( Sum_{n>=0} binomial(2*n,n)^3*x^n )^2.
%F A397472 D-finite: (n+2)^5*a(n+2) = 8*(2*n+3)*(8*n^4 + 48*n^3 + 113*n^2 + 123*n + 52)*a(n+1) - 4096*(n+1)^5*a(n), with a(0) = 1, a(1) = 16.
%F A397472 a(n) ~ Gamma(1/4)^4 * 2^(6*n-1) / (Pi^(9/2) * n^(3/2)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Jun 27 2026
%e A397472 a(2) = binomial(0,0)^3*binomial(4,2)^3 + binomial(2,1)^3*binomial(2,1)^3 + binomial(4,2)^3*binomial(0,0)^3 = 216 + 64 + 216 = 496.
%p A397472 a := n -> add(binomial(2*k,k)^3*binomial(2*(n-k),n-k)^3, k=0..n):
%p A397472 seq(a(n), n=0..15);
%t A397472 Table[Sum[Binomial[2k,k]^3 Binomial[2(n-k),n-k]^3, {k, 0, n}], {n, 0, 15}]
%o A397472 (PARI) a(n) = sum(k=0, n, binomial(2*k,k)^3 * binomial(2*(n-k),n-k)^3)
%Y A397472 Cf. A002897, A395287, A397369.
